            Multi-GPU rigs are quietly disappearing. Most enthusiast builds I see these days run a
            single big card — RTX 4080, 4090, or one of the new 5000-series — because that's where
            the industry has gone. NVIDIA officially killed SLI on consumer cards after the RTX
            20-series, modern games rarely support multi-GPU rendering at all, and the people who
            built these rigs in 2016-2019 are mostly either still running them or have moved on to a
            single-card setup.
          </p>

          <p>
